  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Roll out the dough to a thickness of 1/4 inch (6 mm).",
    "Place the dough on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "Arrange the peppadew peppers on top of the dough, leaving a 1 inch (2.5 cm) border around the edges.",
    "Fold the edges of the dough over the peppers to form a crust.",
    "Brush the crust with the beaten eggs and sprinkle with sugar.",
    "Bake for 25 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.",
    "Let the galette cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes before dusting with icing sugar."
